Foot placement: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with your toes pointed straight ahead or slightly outward.

Bar placement: Position the bar over your mid-foot, and step up to the bar so that your shins are touching the bar.

Grip: Grasp the bar with an overhand or mixed grip, with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.

Posture: Keep your chest up, shoulders back and down, and your core engaged.

Hip movement: Hinge at the hips, pushing your buttocks back and down, while keeping your knees slightly bent.

Grip the bar: Grasp the bar with your hands just outside your shins.

Lift the bar: Lift the bar off the ground by pushing through your heels and driving your hips forward.

Spinal alignment: Maintain a neutral spine throughout the lift, without rounding or arching your back.

Breathing: Inhale before starting the lift, and exhale as you lift the bar.

Lower the bar: Lower the bar to the ground by hinging at the hips and slowly lowering the weight.
